theorem
Th10: (( f | X ) is  Lipschitzian implies ( f | X ) is  uniformly_continuous)
proof
assume ( f | X ) is  Lipschitzian;
then consider r being  real number such that A1: ( 0 ) < r and A2: (for x1,x2 being  real number holds ((x1 in ( dom ( f | X ) ) & x2 in ( dom ( f | X ) )) implies ( abs ( ( f . x1 ) - ( f . x2 ) ) ) <= ( r * ( abs ( x1 - x2 ) ) ))) by FCONT_1:32;
now
reconsider r as Real by XREAL_0:def 1;
let p;
assume that
A3: ( 0 ) < p;
take s = ( p / r );
thus ( 0 ) < s by A1,A3,XREAL_1:139;
let x1;
let x2;
assume that
A4: x1 in ( dom ( f | X ) )
and
A5: x2 in ( dom ( f | X ) )
and
A6: ( abs ( x1 - x2 ) ) < s;
A7: ( r * ( abs ( x1 - x2 ) ) ) < ( s * r ) by A1,A6,XREAL_1:68;
( abs ( ( f . x1 ) - ( f . x2 ) ) ) <= ( r * ( abs ( x1 - x2 ) ) ) by A2,A4,A5;
then ( abs ( ( f . x1 ) - ( f . x2 ) ) ) < ( ( p / r ) * r ) by A7,XXREAL_0:2;
hence ( abs ( ( f . x1 ) - ( f . x2 ) ) ) < p by A1,XCMPLX_1:87;
end;
hence thesis by CKB2:1;
end;
